metadata.name: Rock'n Fall'n #4
metadata.description:
石庭や苔寺がこの作品のインスピレーションの始まりでした。
お寺や神社を散歩するうちに、公園の樹木の樹皮や苔などにも自然と意識が向くようになりました。

スケッチをするように、リアルで写実的な表現をp5.jsで目指しましたが、
技術的に伴わなず、壁にぶつかることも度々ありました。

それを補うように、苔や水、草木や花のような表現を思いつくままに
岩の上を覆うように重ねて遊んでいました。

最初はより自然的な絵に仕上げようとしてましたが、
次第にデジタルで機械的な表現をおり混ぜたいとも思い、
自然なノイズの中に、整列された機械的な要素が見え隠れするような、
対比のある表現を目指していました。

初期段階では想定してなかった思いつき、コードと向き合う中で日々通り過ぎていくような遊びを
色々なパラメータとして振り分けていきました。

４つのモードに分類しています。

・レイアウト
・四季
・描画モード
・その他パラメータ

特別なレアリティなどは設けていませんが、
たくさんのバリエーションを楽しんでいただけたら嬉しいです。



Zen rock gardens and moss temples were the initial inspiration for this piece.
As I wandered through temples and shrines, I began to naturally notice the textures of tree bark and moss in nearby parks as well.

Like sketching in a notebook, I aimed to recreate realistic, detailed expressions using p5.js,
but I often ran into technical limitations and obstacles.

To fill in those gaps, I began layering expressions of moss, water, plants, and flowers on the rocks,
freely experimenting and playing as I went.

At first, I intended to create something that felt more natural and organic.
But gradually, I also wanted to incorporate digital, mechanical elements—
to create a contrast where orderly, artificial forms subtly emerge within natural noise.

Unplanned ideas—fleeting moments of play that came to me while coding—
were gradually transformed into various parameters.

The piece is structured around four modes:
	•	Layout
	•	Seasons
	•	Drawing Modes
	•	Other Parameters

There are no special rarities or exclusives,
but I hope you enjoy exploring the many possible variations.

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #1790
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #665
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Shapes on a Plane #117
metadata.description:
“Shapes on a Plane” explores imaginary structures and worlds through simple shapes. It’s intended for small-scale print.

As a kid I was obsessed with Lego, Duplo, wooden building blocks... anything I could make something with.

I’d spend hours building things, imagining new worlds, new machines, new concepts, then i’d take them apart and create a whole new idea to explore.

To me, this piece to me is a reminder of that time - many days spent exploring ideas with those simple objects - no care for viability, for marketability, for audiences or business. Just pure fun.

Without this time in my life, I doubt I’d have found my passion for creating in the way I do today.

metadata.name: Clew #347
metadata.description:
Thank you for adding me to your collection. Now that I’m a part of your tez fam, please open me in live view, enter ‘9’ or ‘10’, wait, press ‘P’, print me, put me on your wall, and enjoy.
__

Clew is a generative art collection designed for your wall.

When opening live view, you’ll be prompted to choose a render quality (1 for lowest; 10 for highest). The higher quality renders are for printing and zooming in to choose your own sub-composition or explore the details/depth. Higher quality images will naturally take longer to render but will be worth the wait. If you find a partial render particularly nice, you can press spacebar to pause (and unpause) the render. Save a PNG by pressing ‘P’ or a JPEG with ‘J’. Medium and high quality renders are optimized for Chrome desktop and may not function on other browsers or mobile devices.

The processing length varies considerably, depending on the assigned traits. Therefore, not all previews will reflect the final output.

created using p5js

Clew
abstractment, 2022
